description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Junior Sister / Charge Nurse in Critical Care at the Queen Elizabeth the Queen Mother Hospital, which has 9 funded mixed ITU/HDU beds; they will be responsible for overseeing the high standards of care required for looking after critically ill patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Post holder must have completed their ITU endorsement; they must have or be working towards their degree. A minimum of 3 years’ experience in acute care nursing at band 5 is required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be expected to provide professional leadership, advice and guidance for nursing practice in the Critical Care unit. This includes leading in clinical expertise within Critical Care, and being a resource for all nursing staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They will also need to have expert clinical skills, great communication skills and clinical assessment skills. They will contribute to ensuring that the Nurses in the Critical Care Unit are developed to maximize their contribution to the achievement of the Trusts service goals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Deirdre McFarlane Matron on 01843 235054 or deirdremcfarlane@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
